n===International goals===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1. || 11 October 2011 || [[Estadio Jos\u00e9 Antonio Anzo\u00e1tegui|Jos\u00e9 Antonio Anzo\u00e1tegui]], [[Puerto La Cruz]], Venezuela ||{{fb|Argentina}} || align=center | 1\u20130 || align=center | 1\u20130 || [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2014 FIFA World Cup qualification]]<ref name=CAPITAL/>\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n'''Athletic Bilbao'''\n*[[Copa del Rey]]: Runner-up [[2008\u201309 Copa del Rey|2008\u201309]], [[2011\u201312 Copa del Rey|2011\u201312]]\n*[[Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a]]: Runner-up [[2009 Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a|2009]]\n*[[UEFA Europa League]]: Runner-up [[2011\u201312 UEFA Europa League|2011\u201312]]\n\n'''Independiente'''\n*[[Copa Sudamericana]]: [[2017 Copa Sudamericana|2017]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.gazetaesportiva.com/times/flamengo/independiente-e-campeao-em-cima-do-flamengo-e-cala-o-maracana/|title=Independiente \u00e9 campe\u00e3o em cima do Flamengo e cala o Maracan\u00e3|trans-title=Independiente top Flamengo to become champions and silence the Maracan\u00e3|newspaper=Gazeta Esportiva|language=Portuguese|date=13 December 2017|accessdate=12 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n===International===\n'''Spain U19'''\n*[[UEFA European Under-19 Championship]]: [[2004 UEFA European Under-19 Championship|2004]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[https://www.webcitation.org/6GqmIx6KO?url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/the-teams/first-team/fernando-amorebieta Fulham official profile]\n*{{Athletic Bilbao profile|id=557/amorebieta}}\n*{{BDFutbol|752}}\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*{{NFT player|44827}}\n*{{FIFA player|216802}}\n\n{{Cerro Porte\u00f1o squad}}\n{{Venezuela squad 2015 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Amorebieta, Fernando}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Anzo\u00e1tegui]]\n[[Category:Venezuelan people of Basque des